41 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
42 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
43 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
44 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
45 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
46 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
47  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
48 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
49 #else
50 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
51 #endif
52 #endif
53 
54 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
55 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
56 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
57 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
58 #else
59 #error "unknown compiler"
60 #endif
61 
62 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
64 #else
65 #include <cstdio>
66 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
67  do { \
68  fputs(msg, stderr); \
69  DNNL_TRAP(); \
70  } while (0)
71 #endif

85 struct error : public std::exception {
86  dnnl_status_t status;
87  const char *message;
88 
93  error(dnnl_status_t astatus, const char *amessage)
94  : status(astatus), message(amessage) {}
95 
97  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
98 
104  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
105  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
106  }
107 };
108 
110 template <typename T>
111 class handle_traits {};
112 
126 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
127 class handle {
128 private:
129  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
130 
131  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data {0};
132 
133 protected:
134  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
135  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
136 
137 public:
147  handle() = default;
148  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
149  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
150  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
151  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
152 
156  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
157 
161  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
162  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
163  }
164 
166  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
167  T result = _data.get();
168 
169  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
170  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
171  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
172  return result;
173  }
174 
177  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
178 
180  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
181 
184  bool operator==(const handle &other) const {
185  return other._data.get() == _data.get();
186  }
187 
191  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
192 };

502 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
503  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
504  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
505  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
506  } \
507 \
508  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
509  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
510  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
511  } \
512 \
513  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
514  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
515  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
516  } \
517 \
518  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
519  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
520  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
521  return lhs; \
522  } \
523 \
524  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
525  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
526  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
527  return lhs; \
528  } \
529 \
530  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
531  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
532  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
533  return lhs; \
534  } \
535 \
536  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
537  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
538  }
539 
540 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
541 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)
542 
543 #undef DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS

684 struct post_ops : public handle<dnnl_post_ops_t> {
685  using handle<dnnl_post_ops_t>::handle;
686 
688  post_ops() {
689  dnnl_post_ops_t result;
690  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_post_ops_create(&result),
691  "could not create post operation sequence");
692  reset(result);
693  }
694 
696  int len() const { return dnnl_post_ops_len(get()); }
697 
699  primitive::kind kind(int index) const {
700  error::wrap_c_api(index < len() ? dnnl_success : dnnl_invalid_arguments,
701  "post_ops index is out of range");
702  return static_cast<primitive::kind>(
703  dnnl_post_ops_get_kind(get(), index));
704  }

758  "could not get eltwise params");

808  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
809  dnnl_dim_t count;
810  int c_mask;
811  const float *c_scales;
812  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
813  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
814  "could not get int output scales");
815  scales.resize(count);
816 
817  mask = c_mask;
818  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
819  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
820  }
821 
837  void set_output_scales(int mask, const std::vector<float> &scales) {
838  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_set_output_scales(get(),
839  (dnnl_dim_t)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
840  "could not set int output scales");
841  }
842 
844  const post_ops get_post_ops() const {
845  post_ops result;
846  const_dnnl_post_ops_t c_result;
847  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_post_ops(get(), &c_result),
848  "could not get post operation sequence");
849  result.reset(const_cast<dnnl_post_ops_t>(c_result), true);
850  return result;
851  }

855  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_set_post_ops(get(), ops.get()),
856  "could not set post operation sequence");
857  }

919 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
920  friend class primitive;
921  friend struct reorder;
922 
924  enum class kind {
926  any = dnnl_any_engine,
928  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
930  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
931  };
932 
933  engine() = default;
934 
938  static size_t get_count(kind akind) {
939  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(akind));
940  }
941 
948  engine(kind akind, size_t index) {
949  dnnl_engine_t aengine;
950  error::wrap_c_api(
951  dnnl_engine_create(&aengine, convert_to_c(akind), index),
952  "could not create an engine");
953  reset(aengine);
954  }
955 
956 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
957  engine(kind akind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
960  dnnl_engine_t aengine;
961  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(&aengine, convert_to_c(akind),
962  device, context),
963  "could not create an engine");
964  reset(aengine);
965  }
966 #endif
967 
970  explicit engine(const dnnl_engine_t &aengine) : handle(aengine, true) {}
971 
974  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
975  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
976  error::wrap_c_api(
977  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
978  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &engine_q),
979  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
980  reset(engine_q, true);
981  }
982 
984  kind get_kind() const {
985  dnnl_engine_kind_t akind;
986  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &akind),
987  "could not get the engine kind");
988  return static_cast<engine::kind>(akind);
989  }
990 
991 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
992  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
994  cl_context context = nullptr;
995  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
996  "could not get a context handle");
997  return context;
998  }
999 
1001  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
1002  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
1003  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
1004  "could not get a device handle");
1005  return device;
1006  }
1007 #endif
1008 
1011  template <class primitive_desc>
1012  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1013  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1014  }
1015 
1016 private:
1018  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
1019  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
1020  }
1021 
1022  template <class primitive_desc>
1023  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1024  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
1025  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1026  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &engine_q),
1027  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
1028  return engine(engine_q);
1029  }
1030 };

1041 template <>
1042 struct handle_traits<dnnl_stream_t> {
1043  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_stream_destroy;
1044 };
1046 
1048 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1049  using handle::handle;
1050 
1052  enum class flags : unsigned {
1055  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1057  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1059  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1061  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1062  };
1063 
1064  stream() = default;
1065 
1068  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags) {
1069  dnnl_stream_t astream;
1070  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&astream, aengine.get(),
1071  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags)),
1072  "could not create a stream");
1073  reset(astream);
1074  }
1075 
1076 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1077  stream(const engine &eng, cl_command_queue queue) {
1080  dnnl_stream_t astream;
1081  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&astream, eng.get(), queue),
1082  "could not create a stream");
1083  reset(astream);
1084  }
1085 
1087  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1088  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1089  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1090  "could not get OpenCL command queue");
1091  return queue;
1092  }
1093 #endif
1094 
1096  stream &wait() {
1097  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait a stream");
1098  return *this;
1099  }
1100 };
1101 
1102 inline stream::flags operator|(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1103  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1104  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1105 }
1106 
1107 inline stream::flags operator&(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1108  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1109  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1110 }
1111 
1112 inline stream::flags operator^(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1113  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1114  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1115 }
1116 
1117 inline stream::flags operator~(stream::flags rhs) {
1118  return static_cast<stream::flags>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1119 }

1484 
1486  struct desc {
1487  friend struct memory;
1489  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1490 
1492  desc() : data() {}
1493 
1499  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag) {
1500  validate_dims(adims);
1501  error::wrap_c_api(
1502  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1503  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1504  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1505  convert_to_c(aformat_tag)),
1506  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1507  }
1508 
1514  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &astrides) {
1515  validate_dims(adims);
1516  error::wrap_c_api(
1517  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1518  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1519  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1520  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1521  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1522  }
1523 
1527  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &adata) : data(adata) {}
1528 
1530  //
1533  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets) {
1534  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1535  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1536  &sub_md, &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1537  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1538  return desc(sub_md);
1539  }
1540 
1542  desc reshape(const dims &adims) {
1543  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md;
1544  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(&out_md, &data,
1545  (int)adims.size(), &adims[0]),
1546  "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1547  return desc(out_md);
1548  }
1549 
1552  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1553 
1555  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1556 
1557  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1558  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1559  }
1560 
1561  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1562  };

1715 struct primitive_desc_base : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {
1716  using handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t>::handle;
1717 
1718  primitive_desc_base() = default;
1719 
1721  engine get_engine() const { return engine::query(*this); }
1722 
1724  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1725  const char *res;
1726  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1727  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1728  "could not query implementation info string");
1729  return res;
1730  }
1731 
1733  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1734  memory::dim res;
1735  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1736  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1737  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
1738  }
1739 
1741  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1742  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1743  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1744  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
1745  query::exec_arg_md};
1746  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1747  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1748  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1749 
1750  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
1751  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1752  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1753  }
1754 
1757  memory::desc src_desc(int idx) const {
1758  return query_md(query::src_md, idx);
1759  }
1760

1764  return query_md(query::dst_md, idx);
1765  }
1766

1770  return query_md(query::weights_md, idx);
1771  }
1772

1776  return query_md(query::diff_src_md, idx);
1777  }
1778

1782  return query_md(query::diff_dst_md, idx);
1783  }
1784

1788  return query_md(query::diff_weights_md, idx);
1789  }

1792  // purposes.
1793 
1795  memory::desc src_desc() const { return src_desc(0); }
1796 
1798  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return dst_desc(0); }
1799 
1801  memory::desc weights_desc() const { return weights_desc(0); }
1802

1805 
1807  memory::desc diff_dst_desc() const { return diff_dst_desc(0); }
1808

1816  }

1821  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1822  }

1825  engine scratchpad_engine() const {
1826  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
1827  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1828  dnnl::convert_to_c(query::scratchpad_engine),
1829  0, &engine_q),
1830  "could not get scratchpad engine from a primitive_desc");
1831

1833  }
1834 
1836  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1837  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1838  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1839  "could not get attributes");
1840  dnnl_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1841  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1842  "could not clone attributes");
1843 
1844  return primitive_attr(cattr);
1845  }
1846 
1847 protected:
1848  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
1849  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
1850  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
1851  "could not clone primitive descriptor");
1852  reset(new_pd);
1853  }
1854 
1855  primitive_desc_base(
1856  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
1857  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
1858 
1859  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
1860  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
1861  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
1862 
1869  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
1870  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
1871  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
1872  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
1873  if (pd == nullptr) return;
1874 
1875  dnnl_status_t rc;
1876 
1877  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
1878  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
1879  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
1880 
1881  // Check that primitive kind matches
1882  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
1883  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1884  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
1885  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
1886  "could not get primitive kind from the primitive descriptor");
1887  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
1888  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1889  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
1890 
1891  // Check that propagation kind matches
1892  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
1893  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1894  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
1895 
1896  // Something went wrong
1897  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
1898  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1899  "could not get propagation kind "
1900  "from the primitive descriptor");
1901 
1902  // Everything is fine
1903  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
1904  || (rc == dnnl_success
1905  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
1906  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
1907  reset_with_clone(pd);
1908  return;
1909  }
1910 
1911  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
1912  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1913  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
1914  }
1915 
1916 protected:
1917  using base = primitive_desc_base;
1918 };
1919

1935 struct reorder : public primitive {
1937  struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
1938  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
1939 
1940  primitive_desc() = default;
1941 
1945  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
1946  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,
1947  const primitive_attr &aattr = primitive_attr()) {
1948  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
1949  error::wrap_c_api(
1950  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
1951  src_engine.get(), &dst_md.data, dst_engine.get(),
1952  aattr.get()),
1953  "could not create a reorder primitive descriptor");
1954  reset(result);
1955  }
1956 
1960  primitive_desc(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
1961  const primitive_attr &aattr = primitive_attr()) {
1962  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
1963  auto src_md = src.get_desc();
1964  auto dst_md = dst.get_desc();
1965  error::wrap_c_api(
1966  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
1967  src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
1968  dst.get_engine().get(), aattr.get()),
1969  "could not create a reorder primitive descriptor");
1970  reset(result);
1971  }
1972 
1975  primitive_desc(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd)
1976  : primitive_desc_base(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::reorder) {}
1977 
1979  engine get_src_engine() const {
1980  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_src_engine);
1981  }
1982 
1984  engine get_dst_engine() const {
1985  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_dst_engine);
1986  }
1987 
1989  memory::desc src_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
1990 
1992  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
1993  };
1994 
1995  reorder() = default;
1996 
1999  reorder(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
2000 
2004  reorder(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
2005  const primitive_attr &aattr = primitive_attr())
2006  : primitive(primitive_desc(src, dst, aattr).get()) {}
2007 
2008  using primitive::execute;
2009 
2012  void execute(stream astream, memory &src, memory &dst) {
2013  primitive::execute(astream, {{DNNL_ARG_FROM, src}, {DNNL_ARG_TO, dst}});
2014  }
2015 };

2027 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2028  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2029  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_api_mems;
2030  c_api_mems.reserve(mems.size());
2031  for (const auto &s : mems)
2032  c_api_mems.push_back(s.data);
2033  return c_api_mems;
2034 }

2198 
2201 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2202  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2203 
2204  primitive_desc() = default;
2205 
2211  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
2212  const engine &e, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
2213  bool allow_empty = false)
2214  : allow_empty(allow_empty) {
2215  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
2216  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
2217  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
2218  if (!allow_empty)
2219  error::wrap_c_api(
2220  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
2221  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
2222  fetch_impl();
2223  }
2224 
2231  bool next_impl() {
2232  dnnl_status_t status
2233  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
2234  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
2235  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
2236 
2237  fetch_impl();
2238  return true;
2239  }
2240 
2241 private:
2242  bool allow_empty = false;
2243  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
2244  void fetch_impl() {
2245  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
2246  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty));
2247  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty ? dnnl_success
2248  : dnnl_runtime_error,
2249  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
2250  reset(pd);
2251  }
2252 };

2307  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,

2317  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), &src_desc.data,

4492 struct rnn_primitive_desc_base : public primitive_desc {
4493  using primitive_desc::primitive_desc;
4494 
4495  rnn_primitive_desc_base() = default;
4496 
4499  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind,
4500  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind)
4501  : rnn_primitive_desc_base(pd, prop_kind, prop_kind, cell_kind) {}
4502 
4504  memory::desc src_layer_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
4505 
4508  memory::desc src_iter_desc() const { return base::src_desc(1); }
4509 
4511  memory::desc src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::src_desc(2); }
4512 
4514  memory::desc weights_layer_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(0); }
4515 
4517  memory::desc weights_iter_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(1); }
4518 
4521  memory::desc bias_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(2); }
4522 
4524  memory::desc dst_layer_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
4525 
4528  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
4529 
4531  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
4532 
4534  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
4535 
4538  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
4539 
4541  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
4542 
4544  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
4545  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
4546  }
4547 
4549  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
4550  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
4551  }
4552 
4554  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
4555 
4557  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
4558 
4561  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
4562 
4564  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
4565 
4566 protected:
4567  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
4568 
4569  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor from a C counterpart while
4570  // checking that it actually describes the expected primitive.
4571  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
4572  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
4573  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
4574  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
4575  dnnl_status_t rc;
4576  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
4577  error::wrap_c_api(
4578  rc, "could not retrieve rnn_desc from a primitive descriptor");
4579 
4580  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
4581  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
4582  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
4583 
4584  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
4585  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
4586  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
4587  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
4588 
4589  if (!ok)
4590  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "rnn descriptor mismatch");
4591 
4592  reset_with_clone(pd);
4593  }
4594 };
4595 
4599 struct vanilla_rnn_forward : public primitive {
4600 
4602  struct desc {
4603  dnnl_rnn_desc_t data;
4604 
4623  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm activation,
4624  rnn_direction direction, const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,
4625  const memory::desc &src_iter_desc,
4626  const memory::desc &weights_layer_desc,
4627  const memory::desc &weights_iter_desc,
4628  const memory::desc &bias_desc,
4629  const memory::desc &dst_layer_desc,
4630  const memory::desc &dst_iter_desc,
4631  rnn_flags flags = rnn_flags::undef, float alpha = 0.0f,

5961 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {
5962  dnnl_primitive_t result;

5969 
5970 inline void primitive::execute(
5971  stream &astream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
5972  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
5973  c_args.reserve(args.size());
5974  for (const auto &a : args)
5975  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
5976 
5977  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
5978  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
5979  "could not execute a primitive");
5980 }
